        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"th0rgall\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"62658\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/th0rgall/48/48591_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> th0rgall:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>It would be even nicer if a shortcut were available for this action,</strong> since itâ€™s one I perform often. The current method, dragging, gets tedious.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>The current method is not even possible on smaller screens like phones and tablets without connecting a mouse. If I understood <a href=\"https://github.com/signalapp/Signal-Desktop/issues/2454#issuecomment-1309140942\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">this comment</a> correctly, the desktop app used to have a simple button for collapsing the sidebar like the one for collapsing the left panelâ€¦?</p>\n<p>A similar button could solve the issueâ€¦</p>",
